New Section in Income Tax section 206AB
As per Section 206AB of the Income Tax Act 1961, w.e.f 1st July 2021, you will be levied a higher TDS rate if you have :
Not filed Income Tax returns for the last two years; and
Aggregate TDS/TCS credit of Rs. 50,000 or more in each of the two years.
The TDS rate levied will be the higher rate applicable from the list below:
1. At twice the rate specified in the relevant provision of the Income Tax Act; or
2. At twice the rate of rates in force; or
3. At the rate of five per cent.
Linking of Pan with Aadhaar is now mandatory
Every person who has been allotted a Permanent Account Number (PAN) and is eligible to obtain Aadhaar number, must link their PAN with Aadhaar as per provisions of Section 139 AA of the Income Tax Act 1961. Further non linking of PAN with Aadhaar shall make PAN "inoperative" and(1)TDS / TCS would be deducted /collected at Non PAN rate (including cash withdrawal) .
(2)15G/H with inoperative PAN will not acceptable.
(3) Existing Form 15 G / H becomes ineffective till PAN remains inoperative.
To check your PAN - Aadhaar linkage status visit: https://eportal.incometax.gov.in/iec/foservices/#/pre-login/link-aadhaar-status
To link your PAN with Aadhaar, visit: https://eportal.incometax.gov.in/iec/foservices/#/pre-login/bl-link-aadhaar

It's K-Y-C time again!!
As per Reserve Bank of India guidelines, banks need to update identification documents for all customers. Furnishing your latest contact details to your bank is of utmost importance.
For Savings/Salary Accounts:
Please submit a self-attested copy of your passport & visa, address proof & recent passport size photograph, along with a duly filled Re-KYC Updation Form, available on our website under Forms Centre. The above instructions are also applicable to all the joint holders in the account.
For Sole Proprietorship Current Account:
Please submit a self-attested copy of your Individual Identity Proof, Address Proof, Photograph, 2 Entity Proof and Address Proof in the name of firm along with a duly filled Customer Updation Form available at our branches / website- www.hdfcbank.com under forms center.
For Other Non Individual Current Accounts:
Please submit a self-attested copy of documents along with duly filled Customer Updation Form available at our branches / website- www.hdfcbank.com under form centre. List of documents for various constitutions is available in the form.
If you have already submitted the above documents in the recent past, please ignore this message.

*The Reserve Bank of India has clarified that remittance in any form towards participation in lottery schemes is prohibited under Foreign Exchange Management Act, 1999. Further, these restrictions are also applicable to remittances for participation in lottery-like schemes functioning under different names, such as, money circulation scheme or remittances for the purpose of securing prize money / awards, etc. For any further details pls refer below Link-
